There's no better way to see the world than bicycle touring. We head for the Izu Peninsula to enjoy relaxing onsen hot springs, breathtaking views of Mt. Fuji and the blossoming charms of spring.

Japan is known for its natural beauty and the unique culture that developed in these islands, and the very best way to get to know this hidden side of it is to explore it by bicycle.

We take you on a trip through the Izu Peninsula in spring, when the mountains are a brilliant green and the flowers are in full bloom. Our destination is the site of the World Heritage of Mount Fuji. We will tell you about the charm of Mount Fuji and spring in Japan.

Located southwest of Tokyo the Izu Peninsula is a resort tourism destination in a natural setting surrounded by mountains and ocean. It is a hot spring area which is well known in Japan. It has a number of the fishing ports, visited by tourists for its fresh seafood and hot springs.
